= GUI Applications with Root Rights =
Never login as {{Code2|root}} user ({{Code2|sudo su}}) or run GUI applications using {{Code2|sudo application}}. This will fail and is a limitation inherited from Debian. If a user attempts this action, error messages like those below will appear. <ref>
* https://help.ubuntu.com/community/RootSudo#Graphical_sudo
* http://www.psychocats.net/ubuntu/graphicalsudo
</ref>

<pre>
No protocol specified
</pre>

<pre>
cannot connect to X server :0
</pre>

As an XFCE user ({{non_q_project_name_short}} default) use {{Code2|kdesudo application}}. Otherwise, use {{Code2|gksudo application}}. For example.

{{Open with root rights|filename=
/usr/local/etc/torrc.d/50_user.conf
}}

